Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve the @lime{1/2}.

Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/4%tsp}.

When boiling, add the @egg noodle nest{2} to the water and cook until tender, ~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{}.

> TIP: Run the noodles under cold water to stop them sticking together.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the onion and @sliced mushrooms{120%g} to the pan. Stir-fry until softened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Add the garlic, @ginger puree{15%g} and @coleslaw mix{120%g}, then stir-fry for ~{30%seconds}.

Stir the @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, @ketjap manis{50%g} and @water{100%ml} for the sauce into the veg.

Bring to the boil, then simmer until reduced by half and thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Meanwhile, roughly chop the @coriander{1}(chopped, stalks and all).

Add the cooked noodles and half the coriander to the veg pan. Mix together, then remove from the heat.

Squeeze in the lime juice.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Share the veggie pancit inspired noodles between your #bowls{}.

Finish with a sprinkling of coriander and a drizzle of @sriracha sauce{15%g} (use less if you'd prefer things milder) over the top.

Serve with any remaining lime cut into wedges for squeezing over. Enjoy!